[{'text': "R. GARRISON: I'm extremely proud of this project
because it is so revolutionary.", 'start': 0.333, 'duration': 4.55}, {'text': 'The VP of engineering brought to my attention that
we were going to design a self aligning telescope.', 'start': 4.883, 'duration': 5.802}, {'text': "I really didn't know how that was gona... happen.", 'start': 10.685, 'duration': 4.138}, {'text': '- But through the design process we were
able to come up with a great solution.', 'start': 14.823, 'duration': 5.856}, {'text': 'We called it "Sky Prodigy".', 'start': 20.679, 'duration': 1.692}, {'text': 'E. KOPIT: Back when I first got into telescopes
(that was around the early 90s) -', 'start': 47.511, 'duration': 4.076}, {'text': "- computerized telescopes weren't very wide spread.", 'start': 51.587, 'duration': 2.85}, {'text': '- So the problem most astronomers were faced with
was to find objects in the night sky to view.', 'start': 54.437, 'duration': 5.608}, {'text': 'Basically you would take your charts out, figure out in
the sky where an object was in relation to other stars...', 'start': 60.045, 'duration': 5.707}, {'text': "Many people didn't have that kind of dedication
- didn't use telescope that much.", 'start': 65.752, 'duration': 4.457}, {'text': "D. MEDLEY: My first telescope was a 'go-to' telescope
and there was a reason:", 'start': 70.209, 'duration': 3.591}, {'text': '-  When I started I was completely new to the hobby.', 'start': 73.8, 'duration': 3.725}, {'text': 'E. KOPIT: I got to play around with one, I think, in 1990.', 'start': 77.525, 'duration': 2.442}, {'text': '- In one night saw more objects than I
ever had in my life up to that point.', 'start': 79.967, 'duration': 4.658}, {'text': 'First generation computerized telescopes required a user to essentially identify 2 known stars in the sky -', 'start': 84.625, 'duration': 7.115}, {'text': '- and then use the electronics of the telescope
to move to those positions -', 'start': 91.74, 'duration': 4.411}, {'text': '- and then indicate manually
that those stars were centered.', 'start': 96.151, 'duration': 2.987}, {'text': 'D. MEDLEY: It was challenging even
with the technical inclination that I had.', 'start': 99.138, 'duration': 4.438}, {'text': 'R. GARRISON: -And that something that we really wanted to avoid -', 'start': 103.576, 'duration': 2.39}, {'text': "- because we'd heard all the horror stories
that a lot of consumers had with telescopes.", 'start': 105.966, 'duration': 4.553}, {'text': 'E. KOPIT: They would become frustrated,
center to wrong stars, not get a proper alignment...', 'start': 110.519, 'duration': 4.872}, {'text': "D. MEDLEY: One of the results of the efforts to try to
make telescopes easier to use was 'SkyAlign' technology.", 'start': 115.391, 'duration': 5.847}, {'text': 'E. KOPIT: I was blow away because it really
made aligning telescopes much easier.', 'start': 121.238, 'duration': 4.863}, {'text': 'D. MEDLEY: - Basically allowed a user to use any 3 bright stars they could find.', 'start': 126.101, 'duration': 4.809}, {'text': "They didn't have to know the name of the star;
they just had 
 center the telescope.", 'start': 130.91, 'duration': 4.242}, {'text': 'E. KOPIT: - Look in the eyepiece, center this bright but unknown star,', 'start': 135.152, 'duration': 3.133}, {'text': '- press a button and repeat the process 2 more times.', 'start': 138.285, 'duration': 3.062}, {'text': 'D. MEDLEY: After a while, we also realizes that was kind of challenging to do for some people -', 'start': 141.347, 'duration': 5.082}, {'text': '- who had never used a telescope.', 'start': 146.429, 'duration': 1.425}, {'text': 'E. KOPIT: While SkyAlign technology was very successful for Celestron -', 'start': 148.069, 'duration': 3.164}, {'text': "- and represented a leap forward in 'go-to' telescope technology,", 'start': 151.233, 'duration': 3.875}, {'text': '- there was still room for what would be called a completely automated process,', 'start': 155.108, 'duration': 4.46}, {'text': '- which would require no user intervention whatsoever.', 'start': 159.568, 'duration': 3.177}, {'text': 'D. MEDLEY: You know, what you need is a telescope
that can get passed that alignment stuff', 'start': 162.745, 'duration': 3.703}, {'text': '- to get to the good part.', 'start': 166.448, 'duration': 1.26}, {'text': 'E. KOPIT: Celestron has now acquired that technology
through many years of development.', 'start': 167.708, 'duration': 4.977}, {'text': "D. MEDLEY: With 'StarSense' technology
the telescope aligns itself.", 'start': 172.685, 'duration': 4.568}, {'text': "You don't have to get a kink in your neck trying to line up to a bright star. This thing just does it on its own.", 'start': 177.401, 'duration': 4.928}, {'text': "E. KOPIT: The user doesn't need to enter a date, enter a time, enter a location, doesn't need to level the telescope.", 'start': 182.329, 'duration': 5.411}, {'text': 'D. MEDLEY: - You know... like NASA,
they have satellites in space.', 'start': 187.74, 'duration': 3.125}, {'text': 'They lose their orientation, they look out the sky, take
a picture and they figure out where they are.', 'start': 190.865, 'duration': 4.042}, {'text': "This is the kind of technology that's in StarSense.", 'start': 194.907, 'duration': 2.961}, {'text': "R. GARRISON: In approximately 3 minutes
you're up and running.", 'start': 197.868, 'duration': 3.288}, {'text': "E. KOPIT: Once the alignment's completed you can use the telescope's hand controller to select any object you wish.", 'start': 201.156, 'duration': 5.151}, {'text': "The telescope can automatically
move to that object's location.", 'start': 206.307, 'duration': 3.201}, {'text': "This incarnation is, of course, called
the 'StarSense' hand controller.", 'start': 209.508, 'duration': 3.784}, {'text': "D. MEDLEY: It may look  like the old hand control
but it's got a lot more in it.", 'start': 213.292, 'duration': 3.81}, {'text': "I'm pretty sure at this point there are no consumer telescopes sold on the market today -", 'start': 217.102, 'duration': 5.831}, {'text': '- that have built-in mount modeling.', 'start': 222.933, 'duration': 3.028}, {'text': "It's the kind of technology you pay hundreds of dollars for, it runs on a laptop,", 'start': 225.961, 'duration': 4.479}, {'text': "- you've got to have a CCD camera hooked up to your telescope,", 'start': 230.44, 'duration': 2.665}, {'text': "- and it's what advanced imagers use
to be able to get really precise pointing.", 'start': 233.105, 'duration': 4.776}, {'text': "R. GARRISON:  We wanted to keep the cost down, so the consumer wouldn't have to break the bank -", 'start': 237.881, 'duration': 5.432}, {'text': '- to be able to enjoy astronomy.', 'start': 243.313, 'duration': 2.01}, {'text': 'D.
